          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Hi, School should do a awareness for the parents who come n pick the wards, who park their car on wrong direction, speeding, honking, wrong side driving, parking bang on the main road leads to Gurudhwara Sahib hapazardly. Is it what they teach their kids for richly lawlessness? Sad to see the behaviour is being rooted to next gen citizens? Its safety issue as well for road users. How this can be taught to them for courtesious on road? They dont even respect the guards, sadly no respect learnt from their own. They must park one sided leaving smooth traffic for cyclist, cars. Is it a rich bratness to show off at roads? IMHO.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
